{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.6",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 6",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 6 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:2",
      "text": "“Oh that my anguish were weighed, and all my calamity laid in the balances!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:3",
      "text": "For now it would be heavier than the sand of the seas, therefore my words have been rash.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:4",
      "text": "For the arrows of the Almighty are within me. My spirit drinks up their poison. The terrors of God set themselves in array against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:5",
      "text": "Does the wild donkey bray when he has grass? Or does the ox low over his fodder?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:6",
      "text": "Can that which has no flavor be eaten without salt? Or is there any taste in the white of an egg?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:7",
      "text": "My soul refuses to touch them. They are as loathsome food to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:8",
      "text": "“Oh that I might have my request, that God would grant the thing that I long for,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:9",
      "text": "even that it would please God to crush me; that he would let loose his hand, and cut me off!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:10",
      "text": "Let it still be my consolation, yes, let me exult in pain that doesn’t spare, that I have not denied the words of the Holy One.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:11",
      "text": "What is my strength, that I should wait? What is my end, that I should be patient?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:12",
      "text": "Is my strength the strength of stones? Or is my flesh of bronze?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:13",
      "text": "Isn’t it that I have no help in me, that wisdom is driven away from me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:14",
      "text": "“To him who is ready to faint, kindness should be shown from his friend; even to him who forsakes the fear of the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:15",
      "text": "My brothers have dealt deceitfully as a brook, as the channel of brooks that pass away;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:16",
      "text": "which are black by reason of the ice, in which the snow hides itself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:17",
      "text": "In the dry season, they vanish. When it is hot, they are consumed out of their place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:18",
      "text": "The caravans that travel beside them turn away. They go up into the waste, and perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:19",
      "text": "The caravans of Tema looked. The companies of Sheba waited for them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:20",
      "text": "They were distressed because they were confident. They came there, and were confounded.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:21",
      "text": "For now you are nothing. You see a terror, and are afraid.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:22",
      "text": "Did I ever say, ‘Give to me ’? or, ‘Offer a present for me from your substance ’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:23",
      "text": "or, ‘Deliver me from the adversary’s hand ’? or, ‘Redeem me from the hand of the oppressors ’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:24",
      "text": "“Teach me, and I will hold my peace. Cause me to understand my error.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:25",
      "text": "How forcible are words of uprightness! But your reproof, what does it reprove?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:26",
      "text": "Do you intend to reprove words, since the speeches of one who is desperate are as wind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:27",
      "text": "Yes, you would even cast lots for the fatherless, and make merchandise of your friend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:28",
      "text": "Now therefore be pleased to look at me, for surely I will not lie to your face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:29",
      "text": "Please return. Let there be no injustice. Yes, return again. My cause is righteous.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.6.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 6:30",
      "text": "Is there injustice on my tongue? Can’t my taste discern mischievous things?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
